  "storyline": "# Storyline\n\n## Context\n\nThe University of Mumbai experience established the computer engineering foundation behind later analytics and AI work. Coursework and projects covered data structures, databases, NLP, web development, cloud concepts, and image processing.\n\n## Workflow\n\nThe work moved from core engineering coursework into project implementation. Systems were scoped around concrete technical problems, then implemented through database design, application structure, cloud storage, and computer vision logic.\n\n## Technical Implementation\n\n- **Train scheduling system:** implemented scheduling logic with MongoDB-backed storage and AWS S3/IAM concepts.\n- **Social-distancing tracker:** used OpenCV, bounding boxes, and bird's-eye perspective logic for distance monitoring.\n- **Database systems:** built DBMS and schema design foundations through coursework and project work.\n- **Application development:** developed web and backend fundamentals through academic project interfaces.\n- **NLP and image processing:** built early applied AI foundations through text-processing and computer-vision concepts.\n\n## Outcomes\n\nThe experience created the engineering base for later data analytics, machine learning, and systems work, with applied projects spanning scheduling, cloud storage, database design, and computer vision."
